President Obama has announced his intention to nominate Derek Kan as the Director of the AMTRAK Board of Directors. Kan is currently the Director of Strategy at Genapsys and has previous experience as a Management Consultant at Bain & Company and as an Advisor at Elliott Management. He has also served as a Policy Advisor to Senate Republican Leader Mitch McConnell and as the Chief Economist for the Senate Republican Policy Committee. Kan has a B.S. from the University of Southern California, an M.Sc. from the London School of Economics, and an M.B.A. from the Stanford Graduate School of Business.